column4: This is an XML application schema framework; without a profile for the feature types that are implemented, it doesn't get you too far.  NOTE: dataFormat is not a valid OGC resource type (see http://www.opengis.net/def/type/), so these would have to be scoped to osgeo or we'd have to work with OGC to update this.
see above; interesting issue here about whether third place version increments are a different spec.
http is the protocol, so shouldn't this be a service type (it's just a service type that's not tunneled on http)
